when we can get our certifications ?

You will receive your certificate upon successful completion of the AiCE program. To graduate from the program, you must update us on your employment status, complete and submit all weekly tests and milestones, and finish all your assigned peer reviews. There are a total of 12 assignments to complete over the next 6 weeks of the program. Each week, you need to complete 1 test and 1 milestone and score 75% or above on each. If you have met all these requirements, you should be able to access your certificate on Savana.
i had aleardy submitted all test and milestone and had score above 75 %

Congratulations on completing all your tests and milestones with scores above 75%! If you have fulfilled all the program requirements, you should be on track to receive your certification upon successful completion of the AiCE program. The next step would be to update us on your employment status, as this is a crucial part of the graduation process. Keep up the good work!

Hello, what can I do for you?
After submitting a milestone on savannah, what does "ready for a new peer review button do"

After submitting a milestone on Savanna, the "Ready for a new peer review" button allows you to indicate that you are prepared to review a new peer's assignment. This action signals your availability and willingness to provide feedback and assessment on your peer's work. By clicking this button, you are actively engaging in the peer review process, contributing to the learning community by offering valuable insights and evaluations to your peers.
After submitting a milestone on savannah, does "ready for a new peer review" makes your work available for another peer review again

After submitting a milestone on Savannah, clicking the "Ready for a new peer review" button indicates your readiness to review another peer's assignment. This action does not make your own work available for another peer review. Once you have submitted your milestone and completed the peer review assigned to you, clicking this button signifies your willingness to provide feedback on a new peer's work. If you have further questions or need more detailed assistance, please reach out to ALX Africa's team at [ALX Africa Customer Support](https://alxprograms.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/requests/new).

On ALX, we offer a variety of courses tailored to meet different learning needs. Our courses cover a wide range of topics, including leadership, technology, entrepreneurship, and more. Whether you are looking to enhance your skills in a specific area or explore a new field, we have courses designed to help you achieve your learning goals. Additionally, our courses are structured to provide a step-by-step learning approach, offering flexibility for students to study at their own pace. If you would like more detailed information about a specific course or program, feel free to reach out to us for further assistance.

Hello, what can I do for you?
how to get all points in legacy points as it is required ?

To accumulate all points in the Legacy Points program, you need to actively participate and contribute to The ROOM Community by attending events, engaging in activities, and interacting with the ALX platform. Remember, Legacy Points do not reflect immediately after an event, but they will be added to your total as you continue to engage. The more you participate and contribute, the more points you can earn. Keep an eye out for new ways to earn points as the program evolves.
does it mean to fullfill all points in legacy points is key of success in this ai?

Earning all points in the Legacy Points program is not the sole key to success in the AiCE program. While accumulating points is important and reflects your engagement and participation within the ALX community, success in the AiCE program is also influenced by various factors such as your dedication to learning, active participation in discussions, completing assignments, and networking with peers. Legacy Points serve as a way to recognize and reward your contributions, but they are just one aspect of your overall experience and growth within the program.
how to reach within the room of legacy points?

To access the Legacy Points tab on your portal, you need to navigate to your account dashboard on The ROOM Fellowship platform. Once there, you should be able to locate the Legacy Points section where you can view your accumulated points, track your progress, and explore the rewards available for redemption. If you encounter any issues finding the Legacy Points tab, please reach out to our support team for further assistance. Remember, points may not reflect immediately after an event, so continue engaging with the community to earn and redeem your points effectively.

If you are facing challenges locating the Legacy Points tab, we recommend reaching out to our support team for further assistance. fellowship sandtech means what?

Based on the information provided in the Knowledge Base, "Fellowship Sand Technologies" refers to the coding environments known as sandboxes that are assigned to learners. These sandboxes are provided based on the curriculums you have access to within the program. Sandboxes serve as coding environments where learners can practice and apply their skills in a controlled setting. If your curriculum requires the use of sandboxes, they will be made available to you to enhance your learning experience.
how and which ways i will know is my curriculum requires the use of sandboxes? which link to reach out there?

To determine if your curriculum requires the use of sandboxes, you can access the Community Portal. Within the portal, you will find detailed information regarding your curriculum, including whether sandboxes are necessary for your learning activities. If you encounter any difficulties locating this information, you can reach out to our support team via the Community Portal for further guidance and clarification. Remember, our team is here to assist you every step of the way in your learning journey.
lets back on legacy points, till now am unable to fullfill all requirements?

means now can i quit untill you show me again way to fill it?

If you wish to withdraw from the program, you can follow these steps: 
1. Log into the portal using the link provided: [ALX Portal](https://member.theroom.com/community#u/93ed5ad0).
2. Once logged in, navigate to the Legacy Points tab.
3. Fill out the Employment Status form by clicking on the following link: [Employment Status Form](https://member.theroom.com/self-reporting).
4. After submitting the form, you will receive 250 points within 72 hours. Please note that this process can only be done once every 90 days for legacy points.
5. If you still wish to withdraw from the program, you can do so directly on the portal by following these steps:
   - Go to your portal and find the Get Support button under your learning tab.
   - Click on the Get Support button, and you will see the option to withdraw from the program.
Remember, our support team is available to assist you further if you have any questions or need additional guidance.
but i dont want to withdraw at all no, i was asking whether i can let you remind me when this legacy points will be active?

Certainly! If you wish to receive a reminder when your Legacy Points become active, we recommend setting a personal reminder on your calendar or a note-taking app to check back on your Legacy Points status periodically. Unfortunately, we do not have an automated reminder system for individual Legacy Points activation. By staying engaged with the program and regularly checking your Legacy Points tab on the portal, you can ensure that you are up to date with any changes or updates regarding your points. Thank you for your commitment to the program, and we are here to support you along your learning journey.
great! what happen my legacy point remains inactive?

If your Legacy Points remain inactive, we recommend allowing up to 72 hours for the system to update after attending an event or engaging in the program. The delay in reflecting your points could be due to system processing times. We encourage you to check back in a few days to ensure that your Legacy Points have been accurately updated. Remember, your participation and contributions to the program are valuable, and your points will accumulate over time for you to redeem exciting perks and benefits. Thank you for your patience and dedication to the ALX program.
is 175 points enough from the time we begun?

Based on the information provided in the knowledge base, Legacy Points are accumulated by participating and contributing to the ALX program. The total of 175 points you have earned since the beginning can be a significant achievement, considering that Legacy Points are awarded for various activities such as attending events, engaging in the community, and completing milestones. These points can be redeemed for exciting perks and benefits as you continue your learning journey with ALX. Remember, the more actively you participate and contribute, the more points you can earn to unlock rewards. Keep up the great work, and we encourage you to continue engaging with the program to earn even more points and enjoy the benefits that come with them.
thank you for your encouragemen!

We are thrilled to hear that you found the words of encouragement inspiring! At ALX, we understand the dedication and effort it takes to reach milestones in our programs. Your commitment to learning and development is commendable, and we are here to provide unwavering support to help you stay motivated and continue progressing on your journey. Remember, you are part of a vibrant online community where you can interact with fellow learners, ask questions, seek guidance, and share resources. Your success is important to us, and we are here to guide you through challenging concepts and ensure you comprehensively understand the material. Keep up the great work, and know that we are rooting for your continued growth and success! 🌟

what is the meaning of onboarding checklist?

The onboarding checklist is a detailed list of tasks, activities, and resources that learners need to complete or familiarize themselves with during their onboarding week in the ALX AiCE Program. It serves as a guide to help learners navigate through the program's technical tools, understand the program's structure and objectives, and know what is expected of them to maintain good standing in the program. The checklist typically includes items such as accessing the learning management system (LMS), engaging with community spaces, reviewing program materials, and participating in community engagement prompts. It acts as a roadmap to ensure that learners are fully onboarded and prepared to embark on their learning journey effectively.

I'm new to ALX and i didn't understand how peer grading works?

Peer grading is an essential part of the ALX program. It involves fellow learners evaluating and providing feedback on each other's milestones. The process allows for a collaborative learning environment and helps in assessing your understanding of the course material. 

Here's how peer grading works:
1. After submitting your milestone before the deadline, you will be assigned a peer to grade your work.
2. To find out if a peer has been assigned to you, you can click on the specific milestone you submitted.
3. On Kritik, you can see if you have been assigned a peer to grade your work.
4. Once you have completed your assigned peer evaluation, you will see a checkmark next to the assigned peer's name on Canvas.
5. The ALX team reviews all grades during the transition week.

If you feel that your peer has graded you incorrectly, you can dispute the grade on Kritik. However, please note that you cannot change grades on Kritik yourself. The ALX team will review all disputed grades and non-graded milestones.

Am in the AICE program and am really enjoying the experience so far so good but I have health issues that are slowing me down currently. Is it possible to put it on hold and resume later.

I'm sorry to hear about your health issues. If you are facing challenges that are affecting your participation in the AiCE program, you have the option to defer and rejoin a future cohort. By deferring, you can pause your learning journey and resume it at a later time. To initiate the deferment process, you can log into Savanna and follow the steps outlined below:

1. Click on 'Defer to another cohort' and a new pop-up will appear.
2. Ensure not to edit the 'Curriculum', 'Cohort', and 'Period' fields. Leave them as they are.
3. Check the two boxes at the bottom left corner to confirm your deferment.
4. Click on the 'Request deferment' button in red to complete the process.

This way, you can take the time you need to focus on your health and return to the program when you are ready. If you require further assistance or encounter any issues during the deferment process, feel free to reach out to us at https://alxprograms.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/requests/new.
I can't find the defer option

I understand that you are looking for the deferment option in the AiCE program. Unfortunately, formal deferments are not possible at this time for individual delays due to capacity constraints. If you are unable to participate currently, your options are to either withdraw or explore potential special arrangements. 

If you choose to withdraw, please be aware of the following:
- The withdrawal action is irreversible, and all your account details and progress will be deleted.
- Access to program platforms and communities, including Slack and peer circles, will be lost.
- You can initiate the withdrawal process by clicking "Get Support" in your student portal and selecting the withdraw option.

After withdrawal, you would need to reapply for a future cohort when applications reopen, typically in 4-6 months as per the program website updates. While I understand that deferment denial may be disappointing, individual postponements cannot be accommodated at this time due to high program demand. If you require further assistance in evaluating your options or navigating the withdrawal process, please feel free to reach out. I am here to support you through the necessary steps. When we start to learn
Could you please specify which program you are inquiring about? This will help us provide you with more accurate and tailored assistance.
AICE Program

The AICE Program is designed to provide learners with essential AI literacy skills to kickstart their careers. It combines technical knowledge, professional skills, and AI tools training in an 8-week program format. The program includes 1 week for onboarding, 6 weeks of learning, and 1 week for wrapping up the program. Through immersive simulations mimicking real-world scenarios, participants will acquire the skills necessary to succeed in today's digital workforce. Additionally, the program focuses on practical job skills training, communication, teamwork, problem-solving, and developing a compelling online presence for potential employers. The AICE Program is unique in its integrated learning path, aligning with industry demands to create in-demand tech professionals.
What is onboarding week

Onboarding week is an essential part of your journey with ALX. During this week, you will be fully oriented and onboarded into the program. You will gain access to all the necessary technical tools, understand the program's objectives, and learn what is expected of you to maintain good standing. Additionally, you will be enrolled in the Savanna platform, where most of your learning materials will be available. By the end of the onboarding week, you will undergo a test to ensure you have completed all the required steps successfully. This week serves as a crucial checkpoint before delving deeper into the program.
How I can get savanna platform

To access the Savanna platform, you need to go through the ALX Community Portal. The Savanna platform is where you will find all the necessary communication, administration, and learning resources for your program. You can access Savanna by following these steps:

1. Locate your invite email with the subject line [Your AiCE Learning Journey Begins Now!].
2. Click on the portal-sign-up link found within that email.
3. Enter the email you used to apply for AiCE when prompted.
4. Check your email for a unique link sent to your inbox asking you to create a password and sign up.
5. Your profile will then be populated with the information you provided during the application process. You can confirm or edit any incorrect information at this stage.

By completing these steps, you will successfully set up your portal and gain access to the Savanna platform where you can access all the learning content related to your program.

Ai career essentials

The AI Career Essentials program is designed to equip entry-level professionals with essential AI literacy to enhance their careers. It offers a unique blend of knowledge, skills, and character qualities, as well as in-demand AI skills valued by employers today. The program is ideal for individuals starting their careers, those interested in leveraging AI tools to boost their personal brand, and individuals looking to transition to new career paths by enhancing their leadership and professional skills. Through the program, participants will learn how to define and achieve personal career goals, the value of interpersonal skills in the workplace, best practices for CV building, entrepreneurship essentials, effective communication with stakeholders, and the utilization of AI tools in their work. By aligning with industry demands, learners will develop into in-demand professionals with technical knowledge and essential soft skills crucial for success in the modern workplace. The program emphasizes the critical role of AI in job readiness and advancement, equipping learners with vital communication, teamwork, and leadership skills through nine key modules. Participants will gain comprehensive digital proficiency, including the use of AI tools for personal career growth. The program offers a holistic approach to career readiness by combining foundational skills with cutting-edge technology expertise in AI tools.

How to start with the software engineering

To begin your journey with the Software Engineering program, you will dive into a comprehensive curriculum covering essential tools and technologies for developing web applications. The program includes topics such as version control (Git & GitHub), HTML, CSS, Python, databases (MySQL), web development frameworks (Flask), JavaScript, and APIs. You will engage in live learning sessions, hands-on projects, peer learning, and quizzes over a 4-month period, dedicating a minimum of 20 hours per week to your studies. This program is designed to be easily understandable, regardless of your background or experience level, guiding you step by step towards becoming proficient in software engineering. If you are ready to embark on this exciting learning journey, we are here to support you every step of the way.

The ALX AI Career Essentials (AiCE) program is designed to equip young professionals with essential AI literacy skills to enhance their careers. It combines technical knowledge, professional skills, and AI tools training to provide a comprehensive learning experience. The program spans 6 weeks and offers engaging content to develop key 21st-century skills using AI technology. Through immersive simulations mirroring real-world scenarios, participants acquire the skills necessary to thrive in today's digital workforce. Additionally, AiCE integrates AI tools with essential ALX offerings, enhancing learners' abilities to leverage advanced AI tools effectively. The part-time program lasts for 8 weeks and covers 8 meta-skills from ALX Foundations, including leadership, communication, entrepreneurship, and career success training. This holistic approach aims to shape participants into well-rounded professionals ready to excel in their current or future careers. what is the PICS model

The PICS model stands for Problem, Idea, Criteria, and Solution. It is a structured format used in peer coaching conversations to help individuals work through specific tasks or problems. Here's a breakdown of each step:

1. Problem: In this step, the person identifies and describes the specific problem or challenge they are facing.

2. Idea: The individual generates potential ideas or solutions to address the problem. This step encourages creative thinking and brainstorming.

3. Criteria: In this stage, the person establishes criteria or factors that will be used to evaluate the potential solutions. These criteria can be based on feasibility, impact, resources required, or any other relevant factors.

4. Solution: Finally, the individual selects the most suitable solution based on the established criteria. This step involves evaluating and choosing the best course of action to address the problem.

Remember, the PICS model is a helpful tool for structuring peer coaching conversations and facilitating problem-solving discussions. If you have any further questions or need assistance with anything else, feel free to let me know!

What is ALX

ALX, short for Africa Leadership X, is a leading technology training provider focused on accelerating the careers of young Africans by equipping them with the necessary technology and professional skills to excel in the digital economy. ALX is part of the African Leadership Group (ALG), known for its work in developing ethical and entrepreneurial leaders across the continent. Through agile and modular programs, ALX aims to address the talent gaps faced by companies globally by offering in-demand technology career training to empower young Africans for career growth in the digital era. If you have further inquiries or need more detailed information, please do not hesitate to reach out to ALX Africa's team for personalized assistance.
AiCE means?

ALX AiCE stands for ALX AI Career Essentials Program. It is a comprehensive program designed to equip learners with essential AI literacy skills that are crucial for kickstarting their careers in the digital era. This program integrates technical knowledge, professional skills, and AI tools training to provide a well-rounded learning experience that prepares individuals for success in today's digital workforce. If you have further questions or need more detailed information about the ALX AiCE program, please feel free to reach out to us for personalized assistance.

I have a milestone under 75% and I have second chance how I can pass that milestone and how does the second chance work

If you have a milestone with a score below 75% and are eligible for a second chance, you can resubmit the milestone to improve your grade. Remember, when you resubmit a milestone that is overdue, it will be labeled as a "Late milestone" and graded out of 90% instead of 100%, resulting in a 10-point deduction for submitting late. It is crucial to note that the passing score remains at 75%, so ensure you put in your best effort to meet this target.

If you encounter any challenges during the resubmission process or need assistance with removing the previous milestone, please allow us some time as we are actively working on this. You will receive communication from us regarding the next steps.

Can you explainr for me how to pass milestone

To pass a milestone, you need to follow these steps:

1. Complete the activities in your simulation challenge as outlined in the weekly content on Savanna, our learning platform.
2. Ensure you score at least 75% on the milestone.
3. Complete any assigned peer reviews by the specified deadline, typically each Wednesday following the milestone due date by 11:59 pm GMT.
4. If you receive a non-passing score on your milestone, you will have the opportunity to re-submit it for a better score.
5. Passing all 6 milestones with 75% and above is a graduation requirement.

If you have any further questions or need assistance, feel free to reach out to us at [ALX's customer support portal](https://alxprograms.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/requests/new).

How to create a profile on the portal

To create a profile on the portal, follow these steps:

1. Access the portal using the link provided in the welcome email you received with the subject 'Welcome to The Talent Portal'.
2. Click on the link and it will redirect you to the portal sign-up page.
3. On the sign-up page, enter your email address that you used to register for ALX.
4. Click on the "Sign up with email" button.
5. Check your inbox for an email asking you to create a password and complete the sign-up process.
6. Use the link provided in the email to create a password and sign up for the portal.
7. Once signed up, your profile will automatically populate with the information you shared during the application process.
8. Review your profile and make any necessary edits or corrections by clicking on the "Edit" button in your profile.
9. You can update personal information such as your name, phone number, biodata, and experience.
10. Please note that sections like Education and Country cannot be changed.
11. If you encounter any errors or need assistance with editing specific sections, you can contact the support team using the provided form.
12. It's important to know that you cannot change your email address as it is connected to all your records in the ALX training program database.

If you need further assistance or have any other questions, feel free to ask!

How do I defer my course

To defer your course, you can follow these steps:

1. If you wish to defer BEFORE confirming your enrollment and completing your Administration fee, your fee will roll over to the next cohort. You will need to complete payment prior to starting.

2. If you decide to defer AFTER confirming enrollment and paying your Administration fee, your place will roll over to the next cohort, and you will NOT need to pay the Administration fee again.

3. Remember that the deferment cut-off date is at the end of week 2 of your programme. After this date, you will not be able to select to defer and will be considered as having dropped out of your programme.

If you are accepted into the program and wish to defer within the first 2 weeks after the program begins, you can do so through the program portal.

If you encounter any difficulties or require further assistance with deferring your course, please reach out to our team at [ALX Support](https://alxprograms.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/requests/new).

How does Gen AI interact using human language

Gen AI interacts with human language through advanced natural language processing models like ChatGPT and Gemini. These AI tools are designed to understand and generate human-like text responses, enabling seamless communication between AI systems and users. By leveraging these technologies, Gen AI can engage in conversations, provide information, and even assist in creative tasks such as storytelling and content creation. key components of effective prompt engineering

To ensure prompt engineering is effective, it is crucial to consider key components such as clarity, relevance, and engagement. Clarity involves crafting prompts that are easy to understand and follow, ensuring learners can grasp the information or task at hand. Relevance is essential to prompt engineering as it ensures that prompts are directly related to the learning objectives or desired outcomes. Engaging prompts can motivate learners to actively participate and interact with the content, enhancing their overall learning experience. By incorporating these components into prompt design, we can create prompts that are informative, purposeful, and stimulating for learners.

I now have a LinkedIn profile how do I add that to my information

To add your LinkedIn profile to your information, you can follow these steps:

1. Tap the Profile icon in your LinkedIn account.
2. Scroll down to the Contact section.
3. Under LinkedIn, locate your public profile URL. It should start with "https://www.linkedin.com/in". Make sure your URL matches this format.
4. Copy this link and paste it into the designated section for your profile setup.

By following these steps, you'll successfully add your LinkedIn profile to your information. If you encounter any difficulties or have further questions, feel free to let us know!
But the LinkedIn profile link is long, how do I customize it to be short?

To customize your long LinkedIn profile link to a shorter one, you can utilize LinkedIn's feature to create a custom public profile URL. Here's how you can do it:

1. Log in to your LinkedIn account and go to your profile.
2. Click on the "Edit public profile & URL" option on the right side of your profile.
3. On the right side of the page, under "Edit your custom URL," you can see your current public profile URL.
4. Click on the pencil icon next to your URL.
5. Enter the custom ending you'd like for your URL (e.g., your name or a relevant keyword).
6. Click "Save."

By customizing your LinkedIn public profile URL, you can create a shorter and more personalized link that is easier to share and remember. If you encounter any issues during this process, please let us know so we can assist you further.

I'm sorry to hear that you're having trouble accessing the Canvas app on your PC. There could be several reasons for this issue. To troubleshoot, I recommend trying the following steps:

1. Refresh your browser: Sometimes, a simple refresh can resolve temporary issues. Press the refresh button on your browser or use the keyboard shortcut Ctrl + R (Windows) or Command + R (Mac) to refresh the page.

2. Clear your browser cache and cookies: Clearing your cache and cookies can help resolve any stored data conflicts. You can find instructions on how to clear your cache and cookies for different browsers [here](https://www.refreshyourcache.com/en/home/).

3. Update your browser: Ensure that you are using the latest version of your browser. Outdated versions may not be compatible with Canvas. You can check for updates and follow the browser's instructions for updating.

4. Try using a different browser: If the issue persists, try accessing Canvas using a different browser. Google Chrome and Mozilla Firefox are commonly recommended browsers for Canvas.

5. Use an incognito or private browsing window: Open an incognito or private browsing window and try accessing Canvas. This can help identify if any browser extensions or settings are causing the issue.

If none of these steps resolve the issue, I recommend reaching out to the ALX Support Team for further assistance. You can contact them [here](https://alxprograms.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/requests/new). They will be able to provide you with more specific guidance based on your situation.

Is 76 a pass mark

Based on our grading system and principles, the minimum required score to pass a test or milestone is 75%. Any score below 75% is considered non-passing, while any score of 75% and above is considered passing. Therefore, a score of 76% would be considered a passing grade.

Which AI technology is behind self driving cars

Self-driving cars rely on a combination of AI technologies to operate autonomously. One of the key AI technologies behind self-driving cars is **Machine Learning**, particularly **Deep Learning** algorithms, which help the vehicles recognize and interpret their surroundings using sensors like cameras, radar, and lidar. These algorithms enable the car to perceive objects, pedestrians, road signs, and lane markings, making decisions in real-time to navigate safely.

For more specific details on the AI technology behind self-driving cars, you can visit our help center at https://alxprograms.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/requests/new.

Is savanna the same thing as the portal?

Yes, Savanna and the Portal are the same thing. Savanna is the name given to the version of the Intranet used by the ALX AiCE program. It is the learning management system (LMS) where you will access all the AiCE learning material. The Portal, on the other hand, is an online platform that serves as the official tool for navigating the ALX program and The Room Fellowship. It provides access to learning content, allows you to connect with fellow learners, and receive program updates and support from the ALX team.

Please note that Savanna and the Portal are used interchangeably to refer to the same platform.

What are some of the ethical challenges posed by AI that you are most worried or curious about?

Some of the ethical challenges posed by AI that are often a cause for concern include:

1. Privacy and Data Protection: AI systems often require access to large amounts of personal data, raising concerns about privacy and the potential for misuse or unauthorized access.

2. Bias and Fairness: AI algorithms can inadvertently perpetuate biases present in the data they are trained on, leading to unfair or discriminatory outcomes in areas such as hiring, lending, and criminal justice.

3. Transparency and Explainability: Many AI systems, such as deep learning models, operate as black boxes, making it difficult to understand how they arrive at their decisions. This lack of transparency raises questions about accountability and the ability to challenge or audit AI-driven decisions.

4. Job Displacement and Economic Impact: The automation capabilities of AI can lead to job displacement and economic inequality, particularly in industries heavily reliant on manual labor.

5. Autonomous Weapons and Warfare: The development of AI-powered autonomous weapons raises concerns about the potential for lethal decision-making without human intervention, leading to ethical dilemmas and the erosion of accountability.

These are just a few examples of the ethical challenges associated with AI. It is crucial to address these concerns to ensure that AI technologies are developed and deployed in an ethical and responsible manner.

How do you see AI evolving in the next decade, and what societal changes do you anticipate as a result?

AI is expected to continue evolving rapidly in the next decade, leading to significant societal changes. Here are some potential developments and their anticipated impacts:

1. Advancements in Automation: AI will likely lead to increased automation across various industries, transforming the nature of work. Routine and repetitive tasks may be automated, freeing up human workers to focus on more complex and creative endeavors.

2. Enhanced Personalization: AI algorithms will become more sophisticated in understanding individual preferences and behaviors. This will enable personalized experiences in areas such as entertainment, healthcare, and shopping, tailoring products and services to meet specific needs.

3. Improved Healthcare: AI has the potential to revolutionize healthcare by enabling more accurate diagnoses, personalized treatments, and drug discovery. AI-powered systems can analyze vast amounts of medical data, assisting healthcare professionals in making informed decisions and improving patient outcomes.

4. Smarter Cities: AI can contribute to the development of smarter and more sustainable cities. Intelligent systems can optimize energy usage, traffic management, waste management, and public safety, leading to improved quality of life for urban residents.

5. Ethical Considerations: As AI becomes more pervasive, ethical considerations will become increasingly important. Society will need to address issues such as privacy, bias, transparency, and accountability to ensure that AI technologies are developed and deployed in a responsible and fair manner.

It is important to note that these are potential scenarios based on the current trajectory of AI development. The actual impact of AI will depend on various factors, including technological advancements, regulatory frameworks, and societal attitudes towards AI adoption.

2. Personalization: AI algorithms can analyze vast amounts of data to provide personalized recommendations for entertainment, shopping, and more. This can enhance user experiences and save time by tailoring content to individual preferences.

3. Automation and Assistance: AI-powered automation can simplify various tasks, such as automated customer service, chatbots, and smart home devices. This can free up time and improve productivity.

Concerning Aspects:
1. Privacy and Security: Interacting with AI often involves sharing personal data, raising concerns about privacy and security. Users may worry about how their data is collected, stored, and used by AI systems.

2. Job Displacement: The increasing automation enabled by AI may lead to job displacement in certain industries. This can be a concern for individuals whose work may be at risk of being automated.

3. Bias and Fairness: AI systems are trained on data, and if the data contains biases, it can lead to biased outcomes. This raises concerns about fairness, especially in areas like hiring, lending, and law enforcement where AI is used.

What skills do you think will be important to learn or improve upon to coexist and thrive in an AI-driven world?

In an AI-driven world, there are several skills that can be important to learn or improve upon to coexist and thrive. Here are a few skills that can be valuable:

1. AI Literacy: Understanding the basics of AI, its capabilities, and limitations can help individuals make informed decisions and effectively collaborate with AI systems.

2. Critical Thinking: Developing strong critical thinking skills allows individuals to evaluate information, analyze complex problems, and make well-informed decisions, even in the presence of AI-generated insights.

3. Data Literacy: With the increasing importance of data in AI systems, having the ability to understand, interpret, and analyze data can be crucial. This includes skills in data collection, data analysis, and data visualization.

4. Adaptability and Lifelong Learning: AI technologies are constantly evolving, so being adaptable and open to continuous learning is essential. This includes staying updated with the latest advancements and being willing to acquire new skills as needed.

5. Creativity and Innovation: AI can automate routine tasks, but creativity and innovation are uniquely human qualities. Fostering these skills can help individuals find new opportunities, think outside the box, and develop unique solutions.

Some AI-related careers include AI Engineer, Data Scientist, Machine Learning Engineer, AI Research Scientist, AI Product Manager, AI Ethicist, and AI Business Strategist. These roles require a strong understanding of AI technologies and the ability to apply them in various industries.
What can i do with the Alx salesforce certificate

The Alx Salesforce certificate is designed to equip you with skills relevant to working in the Salesforce ecosystem. The certificate can enhance your ability to work with Salesforce tools and technologies, potentially opening up opportunities in roles such as Salesforce Administrator, Salesforce Developer, or Salesforce Consultant.
What does a salesforce administrator do

A Salesforce Administrator is responsible for managing, configuring, and customizing the Salesforce platform to meet the organization's needs. They handle user management, data management, security, customization of objects and fields, workflow automation, and generating reports and dashboards to provide insights for decision-making.
What does a salesforce consultant do

A Salesforce consultant provides expert guidance on how to best utilize the Salesforce platform to meet specific business needs. They analyze requirements, design customized solutions, configure Salesforce settings, and provide training and support to users. Salesforce consultants help organizations optimize their use of Salesforce to improve efficiency and achieve their business goals.

What does a salesforce developer do

A Salesforce developer is responsible for customizing and developing applications within the Salesforce platform. They work on creating custom solutions using programming languages like Apex and Visualforce, integrating Salesforce with other systems, and implementing new features to meet specific business requirements. Salesforce developers play a key role in building and maintaining Salesforce applications to optimize business processes.

I submitted my milestone and my grade is not satisfactory. I think I did better. How can I get it reviewed agai,?

If your milestone score is below 75% and you believe it should have been graded differently, our ALX graders will review it to ensure accuracy. They will reevaluate your milestone to make sure it was graded correctly. Please be patient as this process may take some time, but rest assured that your score will be updated once the review is completed. If you have any concerns or questions during this period, feel free to reach out to us for further assistance.
Do just wait for it to be graded or I need to create a ticket?

If you have submitted your milestone and are waiting for it to be graded, there is no need to create a ticket at this time. Grading can take some time due to the volume of submissions and the grading process. Your milestone score will be updated on the dashboard once the grading is completed. If you have concerns about the grading or if you believe there has been an error in the assessment, you can request a re-evaluation by contacting the program team with a detailed justification for your request. Rest assured that your scores and progress will be updated as you continue in the program.
How do I request a re-evaluation?

If you disagree with the grade you received on a milestone and would like to request a re-evaluation, you can do so by contacting the program team. When reaching out for a re-evaluation, ensure you provide a detailed justification for your request, referencing the rubric and any relevant course materials. The program team will review your request and proceed with the re-evaluation process accordingly. If you need further assistance or guidance on this matter, please do not hesitate to contact us for support.
On what link do I contact the program team?

If you need to contact the program team for any inquiries or support needs, you can do so by submitting a ticket at the following link: [Contact form for ALX support team](https://alxprograms.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/requests/new).
